text: Evanston is a city near the southwest corner of Wyoming. It is the county seat of Uinta County. In 2020, about 11,700 people lived there. Evanston was built in 1868 for the Union Pacific Railroad. The city is along the Bear River and Interstate 80. It is almost 6800 feet above sea level. ==Sources== Category:Cities in Wyoming Category:County seats in Wyoming
title: Evanston, Wyoming
